U.S. Agriculture SecretaryRichard Lyng warned the European Community yesterday it willface serious retaliation if it enacts a new tax on productssuch as U.S. Soybean oil.    Speaking at a news conference before a scheduled speech,Lyng said he did not think the tax, which is still in thediscussion stage, would be approved.    He said the U.S. Would take serious retaliatory actionbecause if implemented, the tax would have a considerableimpact on U.S. Farmers. REUTER&#3;